According to a statement released by the Chinese Figure Skating Association on Wednesday, southwest China's Chongqing Municipality will host one leg of the International Skating Union (ISU) Grand Prix series in November 2023, namely the Cup of China, after two years of absence due to the novel coronavirus. The Cup of China was added to the ISU Grand Prix series in 2003 and staged 17 times. This year's Cup of China is scheduled to take place from November 10 to 12. (Cover: China's Jin Boyang in action during the men's short program at the ISU Grand Prix in Chongqing, Southwest China, November 7, 2020. /CFP)